75. "An irrational man is doomed to fail because he cannot adapt to reality."
76. "Man is a being of volitional consciousness."
77. "To live, man must hold three things as the supreme and ruling values of his life: Reason, Purpose, and Self-esteem."
78. "An error made on your own is safer than ten truths accepted on faith."
