89. "You can evade reality, but you cannot evade the consequences of evading reality."
90. "Man’s basic vice is the act of unfocusing his mind."
91. "The worst guilt is to accept an unearned guilt."
92. "The refusal to think is a declaration of mental death."
93. "Reason is the only guide to knowledge, and knowledge is the only guide to action."
94. "Truth is not a matter of arbitrary choice."
95. "Reality is objective, it exists independent of anyone’s beliefs."
96. "A creative man is motivated by the desire to achieve, not by the desire to beat others."
97. "To understand the world, one must first understand reason."
98. "The pursuit of knowledge is the pursuit of understanding."
99. "Thinking is not an automatic function."
100. "Reason is man’s only means of survival."
101. "One cannot avoid the consequences of evading reality."

