### **Capitalism and Economy:**

102. "Money is only a tool. It will take you wherever you wish, but it will not replace you as the driver."
103. "Capitalism demands the best of every man – his rationality – and rewards him accordingly."
104. "The moral justification

 of capitalism lies in the fact that it is the only system consonant with man’s rational nature."
105. "The most important single central fact about a free market is that no exchange takes place unless both parties benefit."
106. "Wealth is the product of man’s capacity to think."
107. "Money demands that you sell, not your weakness to men’s stupidity, but your talent to their reason."
108. "There can be no compromise on basic principles."
109. "The ultimate goal of all productive effort is to become independent of any man’s decisions."
110. "There are two sides to every issue: one side is right, the other is wrong, but the middle is always evil."
111. "When I die, I hope to go to heaven, whatever the hell that is."

